  "prompt": "Who, according to you, is the best character on Suits? Why?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" character on *Suits* is subjective and depends on personal preferences, but many fans gravitate towards Harvey Specter as a standout character. Harvey, portrayed by Gabriel Macht, is often praised for his charisma, confidence, and sharp wit. His development throughout the series\u2014from a seemingly unflappable, high-flying lawyer to a more nuanced and emotionally aware character\u2014adds depth to his role.\n\nAnother popular character is Mike Ross, whose brilliant mind and photographic memory make him an intriguing underdog. His emotional intelligence and moral compass provide a contrast to the corporate legal world and add layers to the storyline.\n\nDonna Paulsen is also a fan favorite due to her intelligence, loyalty, and memorable one-liners. Her role as both Harvey's confidant and an indispensable part of the firm often makes her a beloved character.\n\nUltimately, the appeal of *Suits* lies in its ensemble cast, with each character bringing something unique to the table.",
